In this message from the President and notice regarding Burma, the President informs Congress that the national emergency between the United States and Burma will continue for another year. The emergency was declared due to the actions and policies of the Burmese government, including the repression of the democratic opposition. The President states that these actions are hostile to US interests and pose a continuing threat to national security and foreign policy. As a result, sanctions against Burma will remain in force. The notice was sent to the Federal Register for publication on May 14, 2009.